    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-09T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-09T03:00:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2241</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MJVA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-09T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 10, 2.25 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The French, British, and Japanese Ministers, considering it imperative to
                    transfer Czech forces from Vladivostok to assist Czechs <pb facs="0362" n="272"
                        xml:id="pg_272"/> in western Siberia, are requesting Russian Legation to
                    arrange with the Russian railway authorities at Harbin for the transportation of
                    these troops by the Chinese Eastern Railway; and upon receiving the expected
                    favorable reply they propose simply to inform the Chinese Government that these
                    forces are to pass through Manchuria.</p>
                <p>In the absence of instructions I have not felt warranted in associating myself
                    with these demarches which contemplate the probability of conflict with
                    Bolshevik forces near Chita and which might therefore be considered as an act of
                    intervention. I beg to request instructions as to the attitude to be taken in
                    regard to this and other movements of the Czech forces in Siberia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJVA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
